<subSubSection id="C3396559FFA7FF9EF36990E4FB30B869" pageId="2" pageNumber="311" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9C36D2FFA7FF9EF36990E4FB30B869" blockId="2.[835,1474,669,821]" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis id="B957EAC0FFA7FF9EF36990E4FC6DB9E9" bold="true" box="[835,952,669,693]" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Large, broadly oval species (body length 
<quantity id="4CDB9B37FFA7FF9EF55890E4FCA4B989" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="4.9" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="311" unit="mm" value="4.75" valueMax="4.9" valueMin="4.6">4.6–4.9 mm</quantity>
). Elytra with subbasal testaceous band broad, straight, not separated from elytral base; elytra without mediolateral spot (
<figureCitation id="13182A57FFA7FF9EF3549084FC69B849" box="[894,956,765,789]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,157,2051,2073]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,190,2035]" captionTargetId="figure-10@3.[97,1463,180,2039]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–9. Habitus of Laccophilus: 1, L. aurofasciatus; 2, L. auropictus; 3, L. ceylonicus; 4, L. elegans; 5, L. girardi; 6, L. hendrichi, new species; 7, L. jaechi, new species; 8, L. javanicus; 9, L. komareki, new species. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5385200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5385200/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Apical part of median lobe in lateral view with distinct bulge on dorsal side (
<figureCitation id="13182A57FFA7FF9EF4AD9164FB0DB869" box="[1159,1240,797,821]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[113,157,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[120,1445,189,1990]" captionTargetId="figure-10@7.[110,1454,186,1997]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 18–35. Median lobe in lateral view: 18, Laccophilus aurofasciatus; 19, L. auropictus; 20, L. ceylonicus; 21, L. elegans; 22, L. girardi; 23, L. hendrichi, new species; 24, L. jaechi, new species; 25, L. javanicus; 26, L. kalimantanensis, new species; 27, L. komareki, new species. 28, L. mahakamensis; 29, L. mazzoldii, new species; 30, L. nusatenggaraensis, new species; 31, L. schillhammeri, new species; 32, L. stastnyi, new species; 33, L. tobaensis; 34, L. tonkinensis; 35, L. wittmeri. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5385204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5385204/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3396559FFA7FF9EF3699124FBB8B8C9" pageId="2" pageNumber="311" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9C36D2FFA7FF9EF3699124FBB8B8C9" blockId="2.[835,1474,861,917]" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis id="B957EAC0FFA7FF9EF3699124FC03B829" bold="true" box="[835,982,861,885]" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">Distribution.</emphasis>
A species endemic to southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3347642FFA7FF9EF5199124FABFB829" box="[1331,1386,861,885]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">India</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49E7F830FFA7FF9EF5539124FA17B829" box="[1401,1474,861,885]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">Kerala</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49E7F830FFA7FF9EF3589104FC23B8C9" box="[882,1014,893,917]" country="India" name="Tamil Nadu" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">Tamil Nadu</collectingRegion>
) (
<figureCitation id="13182A57FFA7FF9EF4249104FBB4B8C9" box="[1038,1121,893,917]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="9.[113,157,2093,2115]" captionTargetBox="[141,1427,190,2077]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs. 40–41. Distribution of the species of the Laccophilus javanicus group" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5385208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5385208/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
